# Function Basics in JavaScript

```javascript
// Function declaration
function greet(name) {
    return `Hello, ${name}!`;
}

// Function usage
const message = greet('Alice');
console.log(message); // Outputs: Hello, Alice!
```

### Key Points:

| Concept | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| Functions | Encapsulate code for reuse |
| Arguments | Input data to functions |
| Return Values | Outputs from functions |

# Asynchronous Operations Using Promises

```javascript
async function loadData() {
  try {
    const response = await fetch('https://api.example.com/resource');
    const data = await response.json();
    console.log(data);
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Fetch error:', error);
  }
}

loadData();
```

### Asynchronous Flow:

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant JS as JavaScript
    participant API as External API
    JS->>API: Sends request
    API-->>JS: Returns response
    JS->>JS: Processes data
    JS->>User: Outputs results
```

> **Note:** Asynchronous patterns significantly enhance the efficiency of dealing with latency-inducing operations.
